    "Coherently, simple effects confirmed that peak wrist velocity was not statistically different in social compared to personal actions in the baseline block 1 (Social -Personal estimate = -0.12, SE = 1.02, t.ratio (34.1) = -0.11, p =.545), whereas it was in block 8 (Social -Personal estimate = 2.75, SE = 1.05, t.ratio (37.6) = 2.63, p =.006).",
